* YOU JUST LET HIM

14
00:01:45,373 --> 00:01:46,373
* JUST A BOY

15
00:01:46,407 --> 00:01:49,177
-[ GROANING ]

16
00:01:49,210 --> 00:01:51,710
-* HE'S JUST A BOY

17
00:01:51,745 --> 00:01:54,215
* HE'S JUST SOME BOY

18
00:01:54,248 --> 00:01:58,648
* HE'S ONLY SOME BOY

19
00:01:58,686 --> 00:02:01,356
UH, NO, NO. UGH!

20
00:02:01,389 --> 00:02:02,659
-IT IS VERY GOOD.

21
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:04,830
-[ LAUGHS ]
-I LIKE IT. I DO.

22
00:02:04,858 --> 00:02:06,928
OH.

23
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,330
HE'S ARISEN.

24
00:02:08,362 --> 00:02:10,932
UH...HEY, BRO.

25
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:12,204
HOW YOU DOING?

26
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:13,533
NO?

27
00:02:13,567 --> 00:02:15,237
I'M RAY. THIS IS LITA.

28
00:02:15,269 --> 00:02:17,569
WE LIVE HERE NOW.

29
00:02:17,605 --> 00:02:19,305
YOUR GIRL SAID TO LET YOU SLEEP,

30
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:20,910
BUT, UH, IT IS TIME TO RALLY.

31
00:02:20,941 --> 00:02:23,941
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE NOT EXACTLY
ON THE LEASE.

32
00:02:23,977 --> 00:02:26,207
-SHE SAID WE COULD
KEEP THE COUCH.

33
00:02:26,247 --> 00:02:27,547
HOPE THAT'S COOL.

34
00:02:27,581 --> 00:02:30,681
-IT'S A VERY, VERY SNAZZY PLACE.

35
00:02:30,718 --> 00:02:33,888
UM, DOES THE REFRIGERATOR
ALWAYS HAVE THAT MUSK TO IT?

36
00:02:33,921 --> 00:02:36,661
-[ CHUCKLES ]

37
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:38,960
WAIT. WHAT'S HE DOING?

38
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:41,502
IS HE GONNA HURL?

39
00:02:41,529 --> 00:02:42,659
DON'T FORGET YOUR BAG!

40
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:48,303
-[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

41
00:02:48,336 --> 00:02:50,936
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

42
00:03:02,316 --> 00:03:04,246
[ KNOCK AT DOOR ]

43
00:03:06,487 --> 00:03:09,557
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

44
00:03:09,590 --> 00:03:11,290
[ SIGHS ]

45
00:03:12,460 --> 00:03:15,560
HAVE YOU EVER DONE SOMETHING
SO HORRIFYINGLY EMBARRASSING

46
00:03:15,596 --> 00:03:17,596
THAT YOU ACTUALLY BLOCK IT OUT?

47
00:03:17,631 --> 00:03:19,831
-UM --
-YEAH.

48
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:21,497
I BLACK OUT ALL THE TIME, BRO.

49
00:03:21,535 --> 00:03:23,395
NO SWEAT.

50
00:03:23,437 --> 00:03:25,707
-BUT DON'T WORRY.
IT WASN'T TOO NOTICEABLE.

51
00:03:25,739 --> 00:03:28,409
YOU ACTUALLY STARTED
TO BLEND INTO THE WALL.

52
00:03:28,442 --> 00:03:29,982
-[ SIGHS ] THAT IS SO LAME.

53
00:03:30,010 --> 00:03:31,610
-DON'T WORRY, YOU KNOW?

54
00:03:31,645 --> 00:03:33,805
WE'VE ALL GOTTEN DUMPED.

55
00:03:33,847 --> 00:03:36,517
GOOD LUCK. [ CHUCKLES ]
I MEAN --

56
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:38,650
-IT WAS NICE MEETING YOU
OFFICIALLY.

57
00:03:38,686 --> 00:03:39,816
-YOU, TOO.

58
00:03:39,853 --> 00:03:41,323
THANK YOU FOR THE STUFF.

59
00:03:41,355 --> 00:03:42,915
-YEAH, I KNOW.

60
00:03:42,956 --> 00:03:48,626
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING,
YOU JUST, UH, LET US KNOW.

61
00:03:48,662 --> 00:03:51,832
[ DANCE MUSIC PLAYS ]

62
00:03:51,865 --> 00:03:55,495
LISTEN, LIFE IS GREAT,
LOVE IS GREAT,

63
00:03:55,536 --> 00:03:57,306
AND YOU WILL FIND IT AGAIN.

64
00:03:57,338 --> 00:03:58,938
IT'S GONNA FIND YOU, YOU KNOW,

65
00:03:58,972 --> 00:04:01,512
BECAUSE THAT'S
WHAT'S GONNA DEFINE YOU.

66
00:04:01,542 --> 00:04:03,882
IT'S WHAT DEFINES A GENERATION.

67
00:04:03,911 --> 00:04:05,651
I DIDN'T BELIEVE IN LOVE,
YOU KNOW?

68
00:04:05,679 --> 00:04:07,819
AND THEN I I MET THIS --
MM -- YOU KNOW?

69
00:04:07,848 --> 00:04:09,478
AND THEN LIKE -- BAM!

70
00:04:09,517 --> 00:04:11,617
-I-- WELL, I THINK
WHAT HE'S TRYING TO SAY

71
00:04:11,652 --> 00:04:13,952
IS YOU'LL --
YOU'LL GET THROUGH IT.

72
00:04:13,987 --> 00:04:15,587
YOU WILL.
-YEAH.

73
00:04:15,623 --> 00:04:16,963
AND YOU STAY WITH US

74
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:19,460
LONG AS YOU NEED
TO GET ROLLING AGAIN.

75
00:04:19,493 --> 00:04:20,763
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?
-THANKS.

76
00:04:20,794 --> 00:04:21,934
I MEAN, YOU GUYS ARE REALLY --

77
00:04:21,962 --> 00:04:22,932
-Shh! Shh! Shh! Shh! Shh!

78
00:04:22,963 --> 00:04:25,903
MI CASO SU CASO, ALL RIGHT?

79
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:27,403
WE KNOW SOME HOT MAMAS.

80
00:04:27,435 --> 00:04:28,835
WE'RE GONNA GET THEM OVER.
-OH, MY GOD.

81
00:04:28,869 --> 00:04:31,069
-I MEAN, I KNOW THERE ARE
A LOT OF GIRLS OUT THERE.

82
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:32,674
I'M -- I'M NOT WORRIED
ABOUT THAT.

83
00:04:32,706 --> 00:04:34,536
IT'S JUST THAT...

84
00:04:34,575 --> 00:04:36,875
CHARLOTTE IS LIKE...

85
00:04:36,910 --> 00:04:39,310
[ SIGHS ]

86
00:04:39,347 --> 00:04:41,847
DO YOU GUYS
BELIEVE IN SOUL MATES?

87
00:04:41,882 --> 00:04:44,622
CHARLOTTE...

88
00:04:44,652 --> 00:04:48,422
CHARLOTTE IS LIKE...

89
00:04:48,456 --> 00:04:51,056
THE MISSING PIECE.

90
00:04:51,091 --> 00:04:52,831
WHEN SHE SHOWED UP, I FELT LIKE

91
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:54,930
I KNEW WHERE I WAS
SUPPOSED TO GO --

92
00:04:54,962 --> 00:04:56,562
TOWARD HER.

93
00:04:56,597 --> 00:04:59,727
HER FACE, HER HAIR --

94
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:01,767
IT WAS MAGIC.

95
00:05:01,802 --> 00:05:05,942
SHE MADE ME FEEL...RIGHT.

96
00:05:28,128 --> 00:05:30,458
-GOOD AFTERNOON.

97
00:05:30,498 --> 00:05:33,668
I'M DR. LAMBERT, AND THIS IS
INTRODUCTION TO ASTRONOMY.

98
00:05:33,701 --> 00:05:36,671
I AM AWARE MOST OF YOU
ARE LIBERAL-ARTS MAJORS.

99
00:05:36,704 --> 00:05:38,074
I GET IT.

100
00:05:38,105 --> 00:05:40,505
IT WAS MY CLASS OR DR. YANG'S
INTRO TO GEOLOGY.

101
00:05:40,541 --> 00:05:41,641
[ SNORES ]
[ LAUGHTER ]

102
00:05:41,675 --> 00:05:43,475
I COMMEND YOUR CHOICE.

103
00:05:43,511 --> 00:05:45,451
WHAT YOU LEARN IN MY CLASS

104
00:05:45,479 --> 00:05:48,449
MAY HAVE NO DIRECT RELEVANCE
TO YOUR FUTURE CAREERS

105
00:05:48,482 --> 00:05:51,522
IN MARKETING OR POLITICS
OR ART HISTORY,

106
00:05:51,552 --> 00:05:54,462
BUT I WILL QUOTE COPERNICUS.

107
00:05:54,488 --> 00:05:57,428
HE'S A FAMOUS ASTRONOMER,
BY THE WAY.

108
00:05:57,458 --> 00:06:00,728
"IF ANYTHING CAN BIND
THE HEAVENLY MIND

109
00:06:00,761 --> 00:06:04,771
"OF THIS DREARY EXILE
TO OUR WEARY WORLD

110
00:06:04,798 --> 00:06:06,998
"AND CAN RECONCILE US
WITH OUR FATE

111
00:06:07,034 --> 00:06:09,044
"SO THAT ONE CAN ENJOY LIVING,

112
00:06:09,069 --> 00:06:10,969
"THEN IT IS VERILY THE ENJOYMENT

113
00:06:11,004 --> 00:06:15,614
OF THE MATHEMATICAL SCIENCES
AND ASTRONOMY."

114
00:06:15,643 --> 00:06:21,423
SO DO YOURSELF A FAVOR
AND PAY ATTENTION.

115
00:06:21,449 --> 00:06:22,849
[ LAUGHTER ]

116
00:06:33,927 --> 00:06:35,527
-CHARLOTTE CATES.

117
00:06:35,563 --> 00:06:37,733
-WHO?

118
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:41,973
-CHARLOTTE.

119
00:07:30,818 --> 00:07:34,488
-SUPERNOVAE HAVE EXPENDED
LESS ENERGY

120
00:07:34,522 --> 00:07:36,122
THAN YOU ON THIS EXAM.

121
00:07:37,858 --> 00:07:40,088
BUT THE QUESTION IS

122
00:07:40,127 --> 00:07:43,057
WILL YOU EXHIBIT
THE SAME BRILLIANCE?

123
00:07:44,898 --> 00:07:46,198
-[ CHUCKLES ]

124
00:07:46,233 --> 00:07:50,273
[ HORNS HONKING ]

125
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:53,713
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

126
00:07:54,675 --> 00:07:58,645
-NO, NO.
YOU HAVE TO WATCH YOUR FOCUS.

127
00:07:58,679 --> 00:08:03,149
YOU NEED ONE MORE SEGMENT.

128
00:08:03,183 --> 00:08:05,793
GLAD YOU COULD MAKE IT.

129
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:12,860
GUESS SHE WASN'T WILLING
TO GIVE UP HER HALLOWEEN.

130
00:08:12,893 --> 00:08:14,903
-WHO?

131
00:08:14,928 --> 00:08:20,298
-THE BLONDE YOU'RE TRANSFIXED ON
DURING MY LECTURES.

132
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:22,673
-I AM LISTENING.
-WONDERFUL.

133
00:08:22,703 --> 00:08:23,873
I'M SURE YOUR PARENTS ARE GLAD

134
00:08:23,904 --> 00:08:27,044
YOUR TUITION
IS BEING WELL-SPENT.

135
00:08:27,074 --> 00:08:29,544
WHY DON'T YOU MAKE IT
WORTH YOUR WHILE

136
00:08:29,577 --> 00:08:31,777
AND TAKE A LOOK?

137
00:08:36,617 --> 00:08:39,247
-[ CLEARS THROAT ]

138
00:08:55,168 --> 00:08:57,568
[ BEEPING ]

139
00:09:01,274 --> 00:09:03,684
OH, UH -- YEAH, YOU TAKE IT.

140
00:09:03,711 --> 00:09:05,151
I'LL -- I'LL GO GET
ANOTHER STACK. SORRY.

141
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:11,790
-HEY, YOU.
-HEY, LADY. HOW ARE YOU?

142
00:09:11,819 --> 00:09:13,289
-[ CHUCKLES ] I'M GOOD.
HOW ARE YOU?

143
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:14,790
-YOU GOT BANGS.
-I DID.

144
00:09:14,822 --> 00:09:16,762
-THEY LOOK GOOD.
-THANK YOU.

145
00:09:16,790 --> 00:09:17,990
-HEY, I'M LOOKING FOR A BOOK.

146
00:09:18,025 --> 00:09:19,925
IT'S CALLED "EVENING"
BY SUSAN MINOT.

147
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,190
-OH, I C-- COULD YOU DO THAT?

148
00:09:21,228 --> 00:09:23,698
SORRY.
[ BEEPING ]

149
00:09:27,034 --> 00:09:28,804
HELLO?

150
00:09:28,836 --> 00:09:30,766
COULD YOU LOOK UP
"EVENING" BY SUSAN MINOT.

151
00:09:30,804 --> 00:09:32,144
I'M IN THE MIDDLE OF AN ENTRY.

152
00:09:32,172 --> 00:09:35,212
-UH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH,
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

153
00:09:35,242 --> 00:09:37,382
[ BEEPS ]
-BEEN A LONG DAY?

154
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:39,210
-APPARENTLY.

155
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:40,606
-SECTION "M," ROW 6.

156
00:09:40,648 --> 00:09:42,918
-M-6. THANKS.

157
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:44,690
[ BEEPS ]
-M-6.

158
00:09:44,718 --> 00:09:46,618
-HEY, ARE YOU WORKING
NEXT FRIDAY?

159
00:09:46,654 --> 00:09:48,794
-ARE YOU DOING SOMETHING?
-HAVING A LITTLE BIRTHDAY PARTY.

160
00:09:48,822 --> 00:09:49,822
YOU SHOULD TOTALLY COME.

161
00:09:49,857 --> 00:09:53,027
-YEAH. THAT WOULD BE PERFECT.

162
00:09:53,060 --> 00:09:55,660
-I'LL SEE YOU THEN.
YOU CAN FINALLY MEET GARY.

163
00:09:55,696 --> 00:09:58,026
-YEAH. SOUNDS GOOD.

164
00:09:58,065 --> 00:10:01,635
WINGMEN SHOULD BE OUTGOING
AND INITIATE CONVERSATIONS

165
00:10:01,669 --> 00:10:03,099
TO HELP ENSNARE
POTENTIAL HOTTIES

166
00:10:03,136 --> 00:10:05,036
FOR THE MAIN PLANE.
-[ CHUCKLES ]

167
00:10:05,072 --> 00:10:08,212
YEAH, "MAIN PLANE" IS DEFINITELY
NOT THE RIGHT TERM FOR YOU.

168
00:10:08,241 --> 00:10:11,081
-AT LEAST I FINALLY GOT YOU AWAY
FROM YOUR "DUNGEONS OF DRAGONS."

169
00:10:11,111 --> 00:10:12,751
-IT'S NOT D&D.

170
00:10:12,780 --> 00:10:13,980
AND DON'T GIVE ME ANY MORE SHIT

171
00:10:14,014 --> 00:10:15,954
OR I'LL ABANDON YOU
MID-FLIGHT, OKAY?

172
00:10:15,983 --> 00:10:17,423
I TOLD YOU, I'M...

173
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:19,420
BROADENING MY SOCIAL CIRCLE.
-RIGHT.

174
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:21,252
-NOW REMIND ME WHOSE --
WHOSE PARTY THIS IS.

175
00:10:21,288 --> 00:10:23,018
-CHARLOTTE, MY HOTTEST FRIEND.

176
00:10:23,056 --> 00:10:24,286
WE WERE IN FRESHMAN DORM
TOGETHER.

177
00:10:24,324 --> 00:10:26,234
-OH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

178
00:10:26,259 --> 00:10:29,059
-HER PARENTS' APARTMENT IS SICK!

179
00:10:29,096 --> 00:10:30,756
HELLO!
-OH, JODI!

180
00:10:30,798 --> 00:10:32,868
-HAPPY BIRTHDAY.
-THANK YOU SO MUCH.

181
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,330
-YOU LOOK AMAZING.
-AWW.

182
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:35,997
-THIS IS FOR YOU.
-THANK YOU.

183
00:10:36,036 --> 00:10:37,806
-MM-HMM.
-HEY!

184
00:10:37,838 --> 00:10:40,068
-ASTRONOMY 101.
UH, DR. LAMBERT'S CLASS.

185
00:10:40,107 --> 00:10:41,877
-OF COURSE!
-HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

186
00:10:41,909 --> 00:10:43,109
-THANK YOU.
-DID DAMIAN GET HERE YET?

187
00:10:43,143 --> 00:10:44,013
-YES. COME WITH ME.

188
00:10:45,813 --> 00:10:48,253
-IT WAS SO AMAZING!
-WAS IT RIDICULOUS?!

189
00:10:48,281 --> 00:10:50,781
I WISH I CAME!
-WELL, IT WAS LIKE...

190
00:10:50,818 --> 00:10:53,748
[ DANCE MUSIC PLAYS ]

191
00:11:16,844 --> 00:11:18,714
-OH, HEY!

192
00:11:18,746 --> 00:11:21,176
UH, I NEVER REALLY KNOW
WHAT TO DRINK, YOU KNOW?

193
00:11:21,214 --> 00:11:22,984
DO YOU HAVE ANY SUGGESTIONS?

194
00:11:23,016 --> 00:11:24,786
-UH, LAPHROAIG.

195
00:11:24,818 --> 00:11:28,088
IT'S THE, UH, 10,
NOT THE 18, BUT --

196
00:11:28,121 --> 00:11:30,161
-OH, THAT --
THAT'S DISAPPOINTING.

197
00:11:31,992 --> 00:11:33,792
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
-HERE.

198
00:11:35,996 --> 00:11:39,226
SKAL.

199
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:42,266
-I'M, UM -- I'M HERE WITH JODI.

200
00:11:42,302 --> 00:11:44,302
DO YOU KNOW HER? SHE'S, UH --

201
00:11:44,337 --> 00:11:47,777
ARE YOU WITH CHARLOTTE?

202
00:11:47,808 --> 00:11:49,778
-ARE YOU IN COLLEGE?

203
00:11:49,810 --> 00:11:52,280
-HEY! WHERE'S MY DRINK?

204
00:11:52,312 --> 00:11:53,952
-UH...HERE.

205
00:11:53,981 --> 00:11:54,981
-[ GROANS ]

206
00:11:55,015 --> 00:11:56,345
-UH, HERE. T-TRY THIS.

207
00:11:58,786 --> 00:12:00,186
-THAT'S GREAT.

208
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:02,290
JACKSON AND MARGOT ARE HERE.
COME AND SAY HI.

209
00:12:02,322 --> 00:12:04,222
-ALL RIGHT.

210
00:12:08,796 --> 00:12:10,126
-[ CLEARS THROAT ]

211
00:12:10,163 --> 00:12:11,833
THESE PICTURES ARE AMAZING.

212
00:12:11,865 --> 00:12:14,095
UM, WHO'S THE PHOTOGRAPHER?
-UH, MY MOTHER.

213
00:12:14,134 --> 00:12:16,104
MY FATHER
DESIGNED THE BUILDINGS.

214
00:12:16,136 --> 00:12:17,906
-W-WOW!

215
00:12:17,938 --> 00:12:20,238
THAT'S, UH -- THAT'S A REALLY
HIGH BAR THEY SET FOR YOU.

216
00:12:20,273 --> 00:12:22,043
-YEAH. THEY'RE FOND OF
REMINDING ME.

217
00:12:22,075 --> 00:12:23,975
THEY THINK MY FUTURE
IS IN BRANDING.

218
00:12:24,011 --> 00:12:25,951
-WELL, AT LEAST THEY'RE CLEAR
ON THEIR DEMANDS.

219
00:12:25,979 --> 00:12:27,279
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

220
00:12:27,314 --> 00:12:28,524
-HOW'S YOUR SCOTCH?

221
00:12:28,548 --> 00:12:32,248
-WELL, IT'S --
IT'S THE 10, NOT THE 18.

222
00:12:32,285 --> 00:12:33,315
[ CHUCKLES ]

223
00:12:33,353 --> 00:12:34,893
HAVE YOU EVER TASTED THE CRACKS

224
00:12:34,922 --> 00:12:37,832
UNDER THE CUSHIONS
OF YOUR GRANDPARENTS' COUCH?

225
00:12:37,858 --> 00:12:40,988
-I THINK THE TERM IS "PEATY."
-HUH.

226
00:12:41,028 --> 00:12:43,498
-I LIKE THAT CLASS.

227
00:12:43,530 --> 00:12:46,100
-OH, YEAH?
-YEAH.

228
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:48,073
MILES OVER MY HEAD, OF COURSE --
MANY --

229
00:12:48,101 --> 00:12:50,071
BUT I-I THINK THERE WAS

230
00:12:50,103 --> 00:12:52,243
NOT ENOUGH SPECIFICITY
IN A PRACTICAL WAY.

231
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:54,042
BUT I REALLY ENJOY
JUST CLOSING MY EYES

232
00:12:54,074 --> 00:12:56,484
AND LISTENING TO THE LECTURE,
YOU KNOW?

233
00:12:56,509 --> 00:12:58,849
-YEAH, YEAH, I DO.

234
00:12:58,879 --> 00:13:00,209
I-I KNOW EXACTLY WHAT YOU MEAN.

235
00:13:00,247 --> 00:13:01,477
