939
00:50:58,423 --> 00:51:00,833
GO HOME.

940
00:51:10,401 --> 00:51:12,201
-WHAT'S UP?

941
00:51:12,237 --> 00:51:13,797
-I'M NERVOUS.
-[ CHUCKLES ]

942
00:51:13,838 --> 00:51:16,138
WHAT ABOUT?
-THURSDAY.

943
00:51:16,174 --> 00:51:18,884
I TOLD YOU A&R FROM URGE
IS SUPPOSED TO SHOW UP...

944
00:51:18,909 --> 00:51:21,279
-RIGHT.
-...AND I'M FREAKING OUT.

945
00:51:21,312 --> 00:51:23,182
PLEASE DON'T BE LATE
TO THIS ONE.

946
00:51:23,214 --> 00:51:25,184
-OKAY.

947
00:51:25,216 --> 00:51:27,386
-WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT?

948
00:51:27,418 --> 00:51:30,518
-OBSERVATORIES OUT WEST,
UP NORTH.

949
00:51:30,555 --> 00:51:32,685
[ CHUCKLES ]
SOMETIMES, THEY POST JOBS.

950
00:51:32,723 --> 00:51:34,433
-THAT'S RAD.

951
00:51:34,459 --> 00:51:36,689
-WELL, YOU NEED A DEGREE
OR RELEVANT SKILLS

952
00:51:36,727 --> 00:51:37,897
FOR MOST OF THE JOBS,

953
00:51:37,928 --> 00:51:39,828
BUT SOMETIMES
THEY NEED A JANITOR...

954
00:51:39,864 --> 00:51:42,874
-[ LAUGHS ]
-...OR -- OR A GROUNDS KEEPER.

955
00:51:42,900 --> 00:51:45,370
UH, THERE'S THIS ONE
AT 10,000 FEET

956
00:51:45,403 --> 00:51:47,473
OUTSIDE THIS REMOTE,
LITTLE TOWN.

957
00:51:47,505 --> 00:51:49,735
IT -- IT'S THE REAL DEAL.

958
00:51:49,774 --> 00:51:52,914
-IT'D BE COOL TO LIVE OUT THERE,
IN THE MOUNTAINS.

959
00:51:52,943 --> 00:51:56,153
I MEAN, IT'D BE LIKE
THE SPIRIT QUEST THE INDIANS DO.

960
00:51:56,181 --> 00:51:57,881
AND WE COULD TRY PEYOTE.

961
00:51:57,915 --> 00:52:00,145
-[ LAUGHS ]
-AND ARE THEY HIRING?

962
00:52:00,185 --> 00:52:02,215
OR DO THEY HAVE A GIFT SHOP?
I COULD DO THAT.

963
00:52:02,253 --> 00:52:03,753
-YOU'D GO WITH ME?

964
00:52:03,788 --> 00:52:05,688
I MEAN, ISN'T THIS
KIND OF ONE OF THOSE

965
00:52:05,723 --> 00:52:07,293
GROWING UP ON MY OWN
SORT OF THINGS?

966
00:52:07,325 --> 00:52:08,885
-IT'S MORE FUN TO GROW
WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

967
00:52:08,926 --> 00:52:12,156
GROWING ON YOUR OWN ALWAYS SEEMS
TO INVOLVE BEING DEPRESSED.

968
00:52:12,197 --> 00:52:14,227
-[ SIGHS ]

969
00:52:14,265 --> 00:52:17,465
YOU ARE WISE BEYOND YOUR YEARS,
LITA MARKOVIC.

970
00:52:17,502 --> 00:52:19,402
-THAT'S WHAT THEY TELL ME.

971
00:52:19,437 --> 00:52:21,667
BEDTIME.

972
00:52:21,706 --> 00:52:23,266
DON'T COME TO BED TOO LATE.

973
00:52:23,308 --> 00:52:24,638
-I WON'T.

974
00:52:27,645 --> 00:52:29,645
-[ LAUGHS ]

975
00:52:35,386 --> 00:52:37,716
-[ SIGHS ]

976
00:52:37,755 --> 00:52:41,285
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

977
00:52:56,541 --> 00:52:57,781
-SORRY.

978
00:52:57,808 --> 00:52:59,308
I CRASHED OUT.

979
00:52:59,344 --> 00:53:02,714
-I KNOW.

980
00:53:02,747 --> 00:53:05,877
WHAT IS THIS, CHARLOTTE?
WHAT -- WHAT ARE WE DOING?

981
00:53:05,916 --> 00:53:09,816
-IT'S US.
IT -- IT'S COMPLICATED.

982
00:53:09,854 --> 00:53:11,364
-THAT'S --

983
00:53:11,389 --> 00:53:13,659
[ CHUCKLES ]
THAT'S AN UNDERSTATEMENT.

984
00:53:13,691 --> 00:53:15,931
-I'M GLAD YOU CAME.

985
00:53:15,960 --> 00:53:19,230
-WELL, YOU ASKED ME TO.

986
00:53:19,264 --> 00:53:21,334
I STILL -- I'M STILL DOING

987
00:53:21,366 --> 00:53:23,226
EVERYTHING
THAT YOU ASKED ME TO DO.

988
00:53:25,303 --> 00:53:27,813
SHOULDN'T THIS BE EASIER?

989
00:53:27,838 --> 00:53:31,408
-SORRY.

990
00:53:31,442 --> 00:53:33,782
I JUST WANT TO MAKE SURE
WE'RE DOING THE RIGHT THING.

991
00:53:33,811 --> 00:53:36,381
-ME, TOO.

992
00:53:36,414 --> 00:53:38,254
-ARE YOU STILL GONNA COME
ON THURSDAY?

993
00:53:38,283 --> 00:53:39,523
-YEAH.

994
00:53:39,550 --> 00:53:42,220
YEAH, IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY.
OF COURSE.

995
00:53:47,758 --> 00:53:49,858
I GOT TO GO.

996
00:54:10,915 --> 00:54:12,775
-AW, THANKS, MAN.

997
00:54:12,817 --> 00:54:14,017
[ LAUGHS ] I GOT IT.

998
00:54:19,990 --> 00:54:21,860
[ HORN HONKS ]

999
00:54:23,394 --> 00:54:26,334
-CAN I GET THE DESSERT MENU?

1000
00:54:32,470 --> 00:54:34,040
-YEAH, NO, I LIKE THAT.

1001
00:55:05,436 --> 00:55:08,936
-* I'M SOMEWHERE

1002
00:55:08,973 --> 00:55:12,883
* YOU'RE SOMEWHERE

1003
00:55:12,910 --> 00:55:16,850
* I'M NOWHERE

1004
00:55:16,881 --> 00:55:20,721
* YOU'RE NOWHERE

1005
00:55:20,751 --> 00:55:24,691
* YOU'RE SOMEWHERE

1006
00:55:24,722 --> 00:55:28,462
* YOU'RE SOMEWHERE

1007
00:55:28,493 --> 00:55:32,103
* I COULD GO THERE

1008
00:55:32,129 --> 00:55:35,069
* BUT I DON'T

1009
00:55:44,609 --> 00:55:50,679
* YOU TELL ME
STORIES OF THE SEA *

1010
00:55:54,785 --> 00:55:59,415
* AND THE ONES YOU LEFT BEHIND

1011
00:56:03,027 --> 00:56:07,467
* AND THE ONES WE LEFT BEHIND

1012
00:56:24,081 --> 00:56:26,521
-[ SIGHS ]

1013
00:56:41,699 --> 00:56:44,569
-HOW LONG?

1014
00:56:44,602 --> 00:56:47,472
-IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.
-HOW LONG?

1015
00:56:49,574 --> 00:56:50,884
I TRUSTED YOU.

1016
00:56:50,908 --> 00:56:53,078
-I KNOW.

1017
00:56:53,110 --> 00:56:54,780
-I-I BELIEVED IN YOU.

1018
00:56:54,812 --> 00:56:56,212
-YOU'RE WONDERFUL.

1019
00:56:56,246 --> 00:56:59,546
I HAVE NO EXCUSE OR DEFENSE.
-STOP, STOP, OKAY?

1020
00:57:02,687 --> 00:57:03,817
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN.

1021
00:57:07,057 --> 00:57:08,787
-[ SIGHS ]

1022
00:57:08,826 --> 00:57:11,856
-BATTING PRACTICE, RIGHT?

1023
00:57:17,535 --> 00:57:20,805
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

1024
00:57:20,838 --> 00:57:23,608
-[ SIGHS ]

1025
00:57:23,641 --> 00:57:25,211
[ SIGHS ]

1026
00:57:45,062 --> 00:57:47,002
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

1027
00:58:31,742 --> 00:58:33,942
[ BLOWS ]

1028
00:58:45,322 --> 00:58:47,022
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

1029
00:58:52,763 --> 00:58:54,163
HELLO.

1030
00:58:57,802 --> 00:58:59,242
-WHO ARE YOU?

1031
00:58:59,269 --> 00:59:02,169
-UH, I'M THE NEW
MAINTENANCE PROFESSIONAL.

1032
00:59:02,206 --> 00:59:04,236
TODD HIRED ME.

1033
00:59:04,274 --> 00:59:06,844
-SO WHEN MY OBSERVATORY
IS BURNED DOWN

1034
00:59:06,877 --> 00:59:08,807
BY A STRAY ASH
FROM THE NEW JANITOR

1035
00:59:08,846 --> 00:59:10,846
WHO HAS NO SCIENTIFIC VALUE
TO THIS FACILITY WHATSOEVER,

1036
00:59:10,881 --> 00:59:13,321
I SHOULD BLAME TODD?

1037
00:59:15,185 --> 00:59:16,815
THERE'S NO SMOKING
AT THIS FACILITY.

1038
00:59:16,854 --> 00:59:19,124
-I-I KNOW. IT'S IN THE HANDBOOK.

1039
00:59:23,360 --> 00:59:25,860
THOUGHT IT'D BE
A NICE WAY TO MEET PEOPLE.

1040
00:59:32,169 --> 00:59:33,999
[ SIGHS ]

1041
00:59:34,038 --> 00:59:35,608
[ KNOCKS ]

1042
00:59:35,640 --> 00:59:36,740
-[ Indian accent ]
COME IN, COME IN.

1043
00:59:36,774 --> 00:59:38,114
WELCOME, MY FRIEND.

1044
00:59:38,142 --> 00:59:39,642
-SAY, UH, WHAT'S ON THE DISH
THIS EVENING?

1045
00:59:39,677 --> 00:59:40,947
-[ Normal voice ]
UGH, S.O.S., BROTHER.

1046
00:59:40,978 --> 00:59:42,678
DEGREE IN PHYSICS --
I MIGHT AS WELL BE

1047
00:59:42,713 --> 00:59:44,723
ANSWERING PHONES AT
A TOASTER TECH-SUPPORT HOTLINE.

1048
00:59:44,749 --> 00:59:46,149
-OH, IS THIS
THE RED-SHIFT STUFF?

1049
00:59:46,183 --> 00:59:49,393
-LYMAN ENERGY ABSORPTION
AND HIGH RED-SHIFT QUASARS

1050
00:59:49,419 --> 00:59:52,119
MEASURING THE UNIVERSE'S
RATE OF EXPANSION OVER TIME.

1051
00:59:53,958 --> 00:59:56,158
WHAT, THEY DON'T TEACH YOU GUYS
THIS STUFF IN JANITOR SCHOOL?

1052
00:59:56,193 --> 00:59:58,703
-NO, IT'S MORE,
UH, PHILOSOPHY --

1053
00:59:58,729 --> 01:00:01,929
YOU KNOW,
LIKE IF THE UNIVERSE'S EXPANSION

1054
01:00:01,966 --> 01:00:03,796
IS HIGHER THAN
THE RATE OF THOUGHT,

1055
01:00:03,834 --> 01:00:06,004
WILL TOKAGAWA FINALLY
HAVE A CHANCE TO GET LAID

1056
01:00:06,036 --> 01:00:09,166
BEFORE EXISTENCE
AS WE KNOW IT CEASES.

1057
01:00:10,107 --> 01:00:11,837
YOUR STUNNING BARB
MIGHT ACTUALLY ZING, BUDDY,

1058
01:00:11,876 --> 01:00:14,036
IF YOU DIDN'T DELIVER IT
WITH A BLEEDING NOSE.

1059
01:00:14,078 --> 01:00:16,248
WEEK IN AND STILL A NEWBIE,
I SEE.

1060
01:00:16,280 --> 01:00:19,350
NOT EVERYBODY'S CUT OUT
FOR LIFE AT 10,000 FEET.

1061
01:00:19,383 --> 01:00:21,253
-[ GROANS ]

1062
01:00:21,285 --> 01:00:23,645
HEY, UH, I WAS HAVING
A SMOKE TODAY,

1063
01:00:23,688 --> 01:00:24,958
AND SOME LADY YELLED AT ME.

1064
01:00:24,989 --> 01:00:27,089
-A LADY LIKE --
LIKE OLDER AND MEAN?

1065
01:00:27,124 --> 01:00:28,734
-SHE WASN'T THAT OLD.
SHE WAS WEARING A HAT.

1066
01:00:28,759 --> 01:00:30,159
-OH, YOU'VE GOT TO
GET OUT OF HERE NOW.

1067
01:00:30,194 --> 01:00:31,804
SHE'S SUPPOSED TO BE
ON SABBATICAL. GO, GO, GO!

1068
01:00:31,829 --> 01:00:33,359
-WHO, WHO?
-HYPATIA! DUDE, OUT.

1069
01:00:33,397 --> 01:00:35,767
NO CIVVIES ON BRIDGE.
GO, THANK YOU, AND COME AGAIN.

1070
01:00:35,800 --> 01:00:36,970
[ GROANS ]

1071
01:00:38,836 --> 01:00:40,666
-[ SIGHS ]

1072
01:01:13,938 --> 01:01:16,038
[ SIGHS ]

1073
01:01:22,446 --> 01:01:24,476
-ARE THE RULES IN THE HANDBOOK
NOT CLEAR,

1074
01:01:24,514 --> 01:01:27,024
OR DO YOU JUST HAVE
NO REGARD FOR FOLLOWING THEM?

1075
01:01:27,051 --> 01:01:28,821
-NO, T-T-THEY'RE VERY CLEAR,
MA'AM.

1076
01:01:28,853 --> 01:01:31,263
-THEN WHY WERE YOU
TOUCHING MY TELESCOPE?

1077
01:01:31,288 --> 01:01:33,088
-I HADN'T COME UP HERE YET.

1078
01:01:33,123 --> 01:01:36,133
UH, TODD WAS SUPPOSED TO
BRING ME, BUT...

1079
01:01:36,160 --> 01:01:37,930
-I HOPE YOU'RE NOT
COMING UP HERE TO SMOKE.

1080
01:01:37,962 --> 01:01:39,502
-I-I DON'T REALLY SMOKE.
-GOOD THING.

1081
01:01:39,529 --> 01:01:41,999
YOU HOLD YOUR CIGARETTE
LIKE A MIDDLE-SCHOOL GIRL.

1082
01:01:44,201 --> 01:01:46,801
-T-T-THEY'RE LIKE MARTINIS,
YOU KNOW?

1083
01:01:46,837 --> 01:01:49,137
I LIKE THE IDEA
MORE THAN THE ACTUAL THING.

1084
01:01:49,173 --> 01:01:51,743
-FASCINATING.

1085
01:01:51,776 --> 01:01:54,406
I'VE BEEN SAYING I'M GONNA
FIX THIS THING FOR YEARS.

1086
01:01:54,444 --> 01:01:56,314
THE GREATS USED TO
BUILD THEIR OWN.

1087
01:01:56,346 --> 01:01:58,016
I SHOULD AT LEAST BE ABLE
TO FIX ONE.

1088
01:01:58,048 --> 01:01:59,748
-THE GREATS?
-[ BLOWS ]

1089
01:01:59,784 --> 01:02:03,454
GALILEO, COPERNICUS, KEPLER --
THE ONES PEOPLE REMEMBER.

1090
01:02:03,487 --> 01:02:05,787
-HYPATIA.

1091
01:02:05,823 --> 01:02:07,793
-THEY STILL CALL ME THAT?

1092
01:02:07,825 --> 01:02:09,455
IT'S AN IRONIC NICKNAME.

1093
01:02:09,493 --> 01:02:11,003
HYPATIA WAS
THE MOST ACCOMPLISHED

1094
01:02:11,028 --> 01:02:12,528
PHILOSOPHER AND SCIENTIST
IN ANTIQUITY.

1095
01:02:12,562 --> 01:02:17,102
PERHAPS IN MY YOUNGER YEARS,
IT FIT.

1096
01:02:17,134 --> 01:02:18,474
-WHAT'S YOUR REAL NAME?

1097
01:02:20,137 --> 01:02:21,837
-JESSICA.

1098
01:02:23,340 --> 01:02:24,940
SOMETHING TELLS ME
YOU'RE NOT HERE

1099
01:02:24,975 --> 01:02:28,275
SECURING YOUR PLACE
IN JANITORIAL POSTERITY.

1100
01:02:28,312 --> 01:02:29,882
-[ CHUCKLES ]

1101
01:02:29,914 --> 01:02:32,784
-SOMETHING ELSE?

1102
01:02:32,817 --> 01:02:34,947
TELL ME IT'S NOT A GIRL.

1103
01:02:34,985 --> 01:02:37,285
-WELL --

1104
01:02:37,321 --> 01:02:38,861
-OH, GOD.

1105
01:02:40,390 --> 01:02:42,490
YOU UNDERSTAND THIS IS
A PLACE FOR NOBLE PURSUITS,

1106
01:02:42,526 --> 01:02:43,886
LIKE THE PURSUIT OF KNOWLEDGE

1107
01:02:43,928 --> 01:02:45,428
AND UNDERSTANDING
OF THE UNIVERSE?

1108
01:02:45,462 --> 01:02:48,872
-AND NOT FOR MARTINIS
AND CIGARETTES?

1109
01:02:48,899 --> 01:02:52,039
-[ LAUGHS ]

1110
01:02:56,573 --> 01:02:59,943
-HOW FAR CAN THIS THING SEE?

1111
01:02:59,977 --> 01:03:03,847
-I'VE OBSERVED AS DEEP
AS 3.2 BILLION YEARS,

1112
01:03:03,881 --> 01:03:07,121
LIKE A TIME MACHINE
PROBING INTO THE PAST.

1113
01:03:07,151 --> 01:03:10,891
EVERYTHING WE SEE COMING IN FROM
THE SPACE AROUND US IS THE PAST.

1114
01:03:10,921 --> 01:03:14,221
EVEN SUNLIGHT
IS EIGHT MINUTES OLD.

1115
01:03:14,258 --> 01:03:18,958
-WHAT ABOUT FIVE YEARS,
SEPTEMBER 14th?

1116
01:03:18,996 --> 01:03:21,066
I'D LIKE TO SEE
WHAT SOMETHING LOOKED LIKE

1117
01:03:21,098 --> 01:03:24,028
ON THAT DAY FIVE YEARS AGO.

1118
01:03:24,068 --> 01:03:26,168
-ALPHA CENTAURI'S
ABOUT FOUR AWAY,

1119
01:03:26,203 --> 01:03:28,143
BUT YOU DON'T NEED
A TELESCOPE TO SEE IT.

1120
01:03:38,983 --> 01:03:41,053
-[ CHUCKLES ]

1121
01:03:45,890 --> 01:03:48,930
-THERE,
THE BRIGHTEST STAR IN THE SKY --

1122
01:03:48,959 --> 01:03:51,529
4.4 LIGHT YEARS AWAY.

1123
01:03:51,561 --> 01:03:53,031
-SO FOUR YEARS AGO,

1124
01:03:53,063 --> 01:03:56,233
I-IT COULD HAVE EXPLODED
INTO A SUPERNOVA

1125
01:03:56,266 --> 01:03:59,136
AND WE'D ONLY
JUST NOW BE FINDING OUT?

1126
01:03:59,169 --> 01:04:01,169
-NOT LIKELY.

1127
01:04:01,205 --> 01:04:03,335
ACTUALLY,
IT'S A BINARY SYSTEM --

1128
01:04:03,373 --> 01:04:06,043
TWO STARS SO CLOSE TOGETHER

1129
01:04:06,076 --> 01:04:08,876
THAT TO THE NAKED EYE,
THEY APPEAR AS ONE.

1130
01:04:13,317 --> 01:04:16,447
SO, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

1131
01:04:19,123 --> 01:04:21,933
-UH, I THOUGHT I'D FIND
MY CALLING.

1132
01:04:21,959 --> 01:04:24,389
-AS A JANITOR?

1133
01:04:24,428 --> 01:04:28,168
-I-I HAD THIS FANTASY

1134
01:04:28,198 --> 01:04:32,598
THAT BEING HERE WOULD IGNITE
SOME PART OF MY BRAIN

1135
01:04:32,636 --> 01:04:35,066
THAT I DIDN'T KNOW ABOUT,
AND SUDDENLY,

1136
01:04:35,105 --> 01:04:38,505
WITHOUT ANY MATHEMATICAL
OR SCIENTIFIC SKILL,

1137
01:04:38,542 --> 01:04:43,012
UH, SOME ASTRONOMICAL SUPERHERO
WOULD EMERGE,

1138
01:04:43,047 --> 01:04:45,647
LIKE IT WAS ALWAYS
MEANT TO BE IF...

1139
01:04:45,682 --> 01:04:49,392
IF I WOULD JUST HAVE THE GUTS
TO FINALLY GIVE IT A TRY.

1140
01:04:49,419 --> 01:04:51,959
-[ LAUGHS ]

1141
01:04:51,989 --> 01:04:54,659
YOU REALLY BELIEVE THAT?

1142
01:04:54,691 --> 01:04:57,361
-YEAH.
-THAT'S NOT HOW IT WORKS.

1143
01:04:57,394 --> 01:04:59,704
-IT CAN.

1144
01:04:59,729 --> 01:05:01,369
IT HAS WITH CHARLOTTE.

1145
01:05:01,398 --> 01:05:02,428
-CHARLOTTE?

1146
01:05:02,466 --> 01:05:04,096
[ SCOFFS ]

1147
01:05:08,205 --> 01:05:09,365
[ SIGHS ]

1148
01:05:12,176 --> 01:05:15,076
MINE WAS NICHOLAS.

1149
01:05:15,112 --> 01:05:17,382
HE WAS A GRAD STUDENT HERE
WHEN I FIRST ARRIVED.

1150
01:05:17,414 --> 01:05:20,284
I COULD NOT CONCENTRATE
WHEN HE WAS AROUND.

1151
01:05:20,317 --> 01:05:23,617
IT WAS -- IT WAS LIKE
THE ENTIRE INTELLECTUAL CAPACITY

1152
01:05:23,653 --> 01:05:25,693
OF MY BRAIN WENT KAPUT.

1153
01:05:25,722 --> 01:05:27,692
-WELL, WHAT HAPPENED?

1154
01:05:27,724 --> 01:05:29,334
-OH, NOTHING.

1155
01:05:29,359 --> 01:05:30,959
-NOTHING?

1156
01:05:30,995 --> 01:05:32,995
-WELL, WHERE WAS IT GONNA LEAD?

1157
01:05:33,030 --> 01:05:34,460
I WAS GONNA BE THE NEXT --

1158
01:05:34,498 --> 01:05:37,498
-HYPATIA OF ALEXANDRIA?
-GOD WILLING.

1159
01:05:37,534 --> 01:05:40,374
I WAS SURE THAT'S
WHAT I WAS MEANT TO DO.

1160
01:05:40,404 --> 01:05:44,174
THERE WAS NO TIME
FOR DISTRACTIONS.

1161
01:05:44,208 --> 01:05:46,708
-HOW DID YOU FIGURE THAT OUT?

1162
01:05:46,743 --> 01:05:49,013
-I KNEW WHERE TO LOOK.

1163
01:05:49,046 --> 01:05:52,346
YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES LOOKING
AS FAR AWAY AS WE CAN

1164
01:05:52,382 --> 01:05:55,622
IS JUST A WAY OF IGNORING
WHAT'S RIGHT IN FRONT OF US.

1165
01:05:55,652 --> 01:05:58,592
-[ SIGHS ]

1166
01:05:59,789 --> 01:06:02,159
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
[ KNOCKS AT DOOR ]

